track_notes: Loop hike its off trail from the Whind Cave to where you rejoin the pass mountain loop trail

The first 1.5 miles is easy on the Wind Cave Trail.  The rest is challenging bushwhack, especially if done when temps are >100F.
My DOWN track (posted separately) is a slightly better route for the small portion between Wind Cave and the ridge.  But this is a rocky, steep hike regardless.
This is a return track to go back via Wind Cave Trail after the bushwhack portion.  See W7JET track for an alternate route.

This route avoids the Wind Cave trail and is almost entirely clearly defined, though not heavily trafficked. It also stays entirely on Tonto National Forest land so can be hiked before the Usery Park opening hours. There are some brief sections of loose sand on the initial ascent but the trail was clear all the way up to the yellow rock face. At that point there is some brief scrambling but some cairns set up that make the route clear (going up the left edge of the yellow section). From there it is a straightforward hike with some switchbacks that finally opens up onto a flat area with a pasture on top. Finally it is a straightforward walk along a defined path up to the summit to the south. I encountered a couple other hikers who had gone up the Wind Cave trail and said it was a lot of difficult bushwhacking once the trail ran out, this seems like a better option.
track_title: Easier route with little to no bushwhacking
